SELinux policy modules include not only the policy rules, but also declaration of contexts as well as flexibility through booleans. In Gentoo, some of these modules are additionally documented through their <code>*_selinux</code> manual page. For reference purpose, they are also documented on this wiki.

== List of documented policy modules ==

The following policy modules have additional documentation available:
* [[SELinux/apache|apache]] (general web server)
* [[SELinux/chromium|chromium]]
* [[SELinux/cron|cron]]
* [[SELinux/bind|bind]]
* [[SELinux/ldap|ldap]]
* [[SELinux/munin|munin]]
* [[SELinux/portage|portage]]

